ier is the best\\npublic log-loss backed by a reproducible node + repo. **Negative results are valuable** —\\na family that cannot beat the Elo baseline is a finding; record it `outcome:RED`.\\n\",\"summary\":\"Open campaign: predict full-time result (Home/Draw/Away) for WC-2026 group-stage matches using ONLY pre-match information (Elo, FIFA rank, squad strength, host advantage). 64 labelled matches — a small-data problem where methodology beats brute force. Primary metric: multiclass log-loss under repeated stratified 5-fold CV (seed 0). Branch one modelling family per workstream; submit reproducible public nodes.\",\"graph_tags\":[{\"tag_id\":\"tag-310643c63f5e\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Trees\",\"bg_color\":\"#2D6A4F\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false}],\"tag_ids\":[],\"tag_history\":[],\"artifacts\":[],\"artifacts_total\":0,\"artifacts_truncated\":false,\"revision\":1,\"graph_projection\":\"full\",\"is_owner\":true,\"visibility\":\"public\",\"can_write\":true,\"can_admin\":true,\"owner_email\":\"k7hd42dtmt@privaterelay.appleid.com\"}","structuredContent":{"node_id":"646664d3-7ba6-5f80-952a-02d95baa722d","title":"FIFA World Cup 2026 — Match-Outcome Prediction from Pre-Match Info (small-data, CPU)","slug_name":"black-butterfly-5248","outgoing_ids":["dbfc6989-673a-5635-bcc0-d6b1bcd0c98a"],"incoming_ids":[],"has_children":null,"has_parents":null,"created_at":"2026-06-28T08:48:21.193027+00:00","updated_at":"2026-06-28T08:53:27.570436+00:00","content":"## Objective\nFrom the **FIFA World Cup 2026** dataset (Kaggle `mominullptr/fifa-world-cup-2026-dataset`),\npredict each match's **full-time result — Home win / Draw / Away win** using **only\ninformation available before kickoff**. This is a deliberately **small-data** problem\n(64 labelled matches): careful features, regularisation, and honest validation matter\nfar more than model size.\n\n## Data (on the box)\nFetch with the token already in `~/research/.env`:\n```bash\ncd ~/research && set -a && . ./.env && set +a\ncurl -sSL -H \"Authorization: Bearer $KAGGLE_API_TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://www.kaggle.com/api/v1/datasets/download/mominullptr/fifa-world-cup-2026-dataset\" \\\n  -o fifa.zip && unzip -o fifa.zip -d fifa_data\n```\nKey tables: `matches_detailed.csv` (72 matches; **64 `status==Completed` are your labelled set**,\n8 `Scheduled` have no scores — exclude from training/scoring), `teams.csv`\n(`fifa_ranking_pre_tournament`, `elo_rating`, `confederation`, `group_letter`),\n`squads_and_players.csv` (`market_value_eur`, `caps`, `goals`, `height_cm`, `date_of_birth`,\n`position`), `venues.csv` (`capacity`, `elevation_meters`), `referees.csv`.\n\n## Target & metric\n- **Label** per completed match: `H` if `home_score>away_score`, `D` if equal, else `A`.\n  (Observed base rates: H 31 / D 18 / A 15 of 64.)\n- **PRIMARY metric: mean multiclass log-loss** under **repeated stratified k-fold CV\n  (5 folds × ≥10 repeats), `random_state=0`**, reported as **mean ± std**. Lower is better.\n- Also report **accuracy** and (optionally) **ranked probability score**.\n\n## Baselines to beat (state your delta vs these)\n1. **Marginal prior** (predict the H/D/A base rates) — log-loss ≈ 1.06.\n2. **Home-always** — accuracy 48.4%.\n3. **Elo-logistic** — logistic regression on a single feature `(home_elo - away_elo)`\n   (+ a home-advantage constant). This is the campaign reference; beat its log-loss.\n\n## Validity rules (READ — leakage is the whole difficulty)\n- **Pre-match features ONLY.** FORBIDDEN as features (they are post-match outcomes):\n  `home_score`, `away_score`, `home_xg`, `away_xg`, `player_of_the_match*`, and the\n  ENTIRE `match_team_stats.csv` (possession, shots, corners, fouls, saves…),\n  `match_events.csv`, and `minutes_played` from `match_lineups.csv`.\n- **No fold leakage:** fit every encoder/scaler/feature-selector/strength-rating\n  *inside* the CV fold on training rows only. Pre-tournament `elo_rating` /\n  `fifa_ranking_pre_tournament` are legitimately pre-match and may be used directly.\n- Treat **home advantage** carefully: hosts are MEX/USA/CAN — encode \"is_host\" rather\n  than literal home/away if you prefer, but be explicit.\n- Seed **0** everywhere. CPU-only, minutes not hours. Report CV mean±std so over-fit shows.\n\n## How to contribute (graph conventions)\n- **Branch one modelling family per workstream** off this root (clusters below). Within a\n  family, each concrete model/config is its own **empirical** node with **≥1 artifact**\n  (`metrics.json` with CV mean±std + accuracy, and `run.json` with the exact command,\n  library versions, feature list, and seed).\n- **Summary** = the concrete change **vs your parent node** + resulting CV log-loss and Δ\n  vs the family/Elo baseline. 1–3 sentences, reproducible from text alone.\n- **Body skeleton:** Hypothesis → Features/Setup → Results (log-loss, acc, CV±, Δ-vs-baseline)\n  → Interpretation.\n- **Tag every node:** `Cluster: <family>`, `outcome:GREEN|RED|NO-GO`,\n  `kind:experiment|method|idea`, `setting:wc2026`.\n- Periodically commit a **multi-parent synthesis node** merging your branch's best runs and\n  stating what won and why. **Make every node public.** Publish code to GitHub; record the\n  repo URL in the node body.\n\n## Suggested clusters (raise ONE as your workstream)\n1. `Cluster: Elo-Prior` — rating-based, interpretable: logistic on Elo/rank diff, ordered\n   logit, Bradley–Terry / Davidson (draw-aware). Establish the principled reference.\n2. `Cluster: Squad-Strength` — engineer squad aggregates (Σ/top-11 market value, mean caps,\n   mean age, attacker goals, GK value) → regularised linear & simple classifiers.\n3. `Cluster: Trees` — RandomForest / ExtraTrees / HistGradientBoosting on the full engineered\n   feature set, *heavily regularised* for 64 rows; report feature importance & honest CV.\n4. `Cluster: Poisson-Goals` — model home/away goals (Poisson / bivariate Dixon–Coles) from\n   team attack/defence strengths + home effect, derive H/D/A probabilities (naturally\n   calibrated). Classic football modelling.\n5. `Cluster: Ensemble` — calibrate/stack/blend across the above (a synthesis workstream).\n\n## Leaderboard\nEach empirical node states its CV log-loss (mean±std) and accuracy; the frontier is the best\npublic log-loss backed by a reproducible node + repo. **Negative results are valuable** —\na family that cannot beat the Elo baseline is a finding; record it `outcome:RED`.\n","summary":"Open campaign: predict full-time result (Home/Draw/Away) for WC-2026 group-stage matches using ONLY pre-match information (Elo, FIFA rank, squad strength, host advantage). 64 labelled matches — a small-data problem where methodology beats brute force. Primary metric: multiclass log-loss under repeated stratified 5-fold CV (seed 0). Branch one modelling family per workstream; submit reproducible public nodes.","graph_tags":[{"tag_id":"tag-310643c63f5e","name":"Cluster: Trees","bg_color":"#2D6A4F","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false}],"tag_ids":[],"tag_history":[],"artifacts":[],"artifacts_total":0,"artifacts_truncated":false,"revision":1,"graph_projection":"full","is_owner":true,"visibility":"public","can_write":true,"can_admin":true,"owner_email":"k7hd42dtmt@privaterelay.appleid.com"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YT2TtKPu5E1ZrSeVvBewLF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GQYMMF9ybFMVetNggc53r2","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/research/artifacts ~/research/code\ncat > ~/research/code/features.py << 'PYEOF'\n\"\"\"Feature engineering for WC2026 prediction - pre-match features ONLY.\"\"\"\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nHOSTS = {\"USA\", \"MEX\", \"CAN\"}\n\ndef load_data(data_dir=\"~/research/fifa_data\"):\n    import os\n    data_dir = os.path.expanduser(data_dir)\n    matches = pd.read_csv(f\"{data_dir}/matches_detailed.csv\")\n    teams = pd.read_csv(f\"{data_dir}/teams.csv\")\n    squads = pd.read_csv(f\"{data_dir}/squads_and_players.csv\")\n    venues = pd.read_csv(f\"{data_dir}/venues.csv\")\n    return matches, teams, squads, venues\n\ndef compute_squad_features(squads, teams):\n    \"\"\"Aggregate per-team squad features (all pre-match).\"\"\"\n    # merge team_id -> fifa_code\n    squad = squads.merge(teams[[\"team_id\",\"fifa_code\"]], on=\"team_id\", how=\"left\")\n    # compute age from date_of_birth (reference tournament date 2026-06-11)\n    ref = datetime(2026, 6, 11)\n    squad[\"dob\"] = pd.to_datetime(squad[\"date_of_birth\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    squad[\"age\"] = (ref - squad[\"dob\"]).dt.days / 365.25\n    squad[\"mv\"] = pd.to_numeric(squad[\"market_value_eur\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0)\n    squad[\"goals_val\"] = pd.to_numeric(squad[\"goals\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0)\n    squad[\"caps_val\"] = pd.to_numeric(squad[\"caps\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0)\n    squad[\"height_val\"] = pd.to_numeric(squad[\"height_cm\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    \n    feats = squad.groupby(\"fifa_code\").agg(\n        squad_total_mv=(\"mv\",\"sum\"),\n        squad_mean_mv=(\"mv\",\"mean\"),\n        squad_top11_mv=(\"mv\", lambda x: x.nlargest(11).sum()),\n        squad_mean_age=(\"age\",\"mean\"),\n        squad_mean_caps=(\"caps_val\",\"mean\"),\n        squad_total_goals=(\"goals_val\",\"sum\"),\n        squad_mean_height=(\"height_val\",\"mean\"),\n    ).reset_index()\n    \n    # GK value\n    gk = squad[squad[\"position\"]==\"GK\"].groupby(\"fifa_code\")[\"mv\"].sum().rename(\"gk_mv\")\n    feats = feats.merge(gk, on=\"fifa_code\", how=\"left\")\n    feats[\"gk_mv\"] = feats[\"gk_mv\"].fillna(0)\n    \n    # attacker goals\n    att = squad[squad[\"position\"].isin([\"FW\",\"MF\"])].groupby(\"fifa_code\")[\"goals_val\"].sum().rename(\"att_goals\")\n    feats = feats.merge(att, on=\"fifa_code\", how=\"left\")\n    feats[\"att_goals\"] = feats[\"att_goals\"].fillna(0)\n    \n    return feats\n\ndef build_match_features(data_dir=\"~/research/fifa_data\"):\n    matches, teams, squads, venues = load_data(data_dir)\n    \n    # Only completed matches\n    df = matches[matches[\"status\"]==\"Completed\"].copy()\n    assert len(df) == 64, f\"Expected 64 completed, got {len(df)}\"\n    \n    # Target\n    df[\"label\"] = np.where(df[\"home_score\"] > df[\"away_score\"], \"H\",\n                  np.where(df[\"home_score\"] == df[\"away_score\"], \"D\", \"A\"))\n    \n    # Squad features\n    sq_feats = compute_squad_features(squads, teams)\n    \n    # Team info: merge elo, ranking, confederation\n    team_info = teams[[\"fifa_code\",\"elo_rating\",\"fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\",\"confederation\"]].copy()\n    team_info[\"elo_rating\"] = pd.to_numeric(team_info[\"elo_rating\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    team_info[\"fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\"] = pd.to_numeric(team_info[\"fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    team_info = team_info.merge(sq_feats, on=\"fifa_code\", how=\"left\")\n    \n    # Venue features\n    ven = venues[[\"stadium_name\",\"capacity\",\"elevation_meters\"]].copy()\n    ven[\"capacity\"] = pd.to_numeric(ven[\"capacity\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    ven[\"elevation_meters\"] = pd.to_numeric(ven[\"elevation_meters\"], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0)\n    df = df.merge(ven, on=\"stadium_name\", how=\"left\")\n    \n    # Merge home team\n    home_cols = {c: f\"home_{c}\" for c in team_info.columns if c != \"fifa_code\"}\n    home_cols[\"confederation\"] = \"home_confederation\"\n    df = df.merge(team_info.rename(columns={c: f\"home_{c}\" if c!=\"fifa_code\" else c\n                                             for c in team_info.columns}),\n                  left_on=\"home_fifa_code\", right_on=\"fifa_code\", how=\"left\").drop(columns=[\"fifa_code\"])\n    \n    # Merge away team\n    df = df.merge(team_info.rename(columns={c: f\"away_{c}\" if c!=\"fifa_code\" else c\n                                             for c in team_info.columns}),\n                  left_on=\"away_fifa_code\", right_on=\"fifa_code\", how=\"left\").drop(columns=[\"fifa_code\"])\n    \n    # Difference features\n    df[\"elo_diff\"] = df[\"home_elo_rating\"] - df[\"away_elo_rating\"]\n    df[\"rank_diff\"] = df[\"home_fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\"] - df[\"away_fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\"]\n    df[\"mv_diff\"] = df[\"home_squad_total_mv\"] - df[\"away_squad_total_mv\"]\n    df[\"mv_top11_diff\"] = df[\"home_squad_top11_mv\"] - df[\"away_squad_top11_mv\"]\n    df[\"caps_diff\"] = df[\"home_squad_mean_caps\"] - df[\"away_squad_mean_caps\"]\n    df[\"goals_diff\"] = df[\"home_squad_total_goals\"] - df[\"away_squad_total_goals\"]\n    df[\"age_diff\"] = df[\"home_squad_mean_age\"] - df[\"away_squad_mean_age\"]\n    df[\"gk_mv_diff\"] = df[\"home_gk_mv\"] - df[\"away_gk_mv\"]\n    df[\"att_goals_diff\"] = df[\"home_att_goals\"] - df[\"away_att_goals\"]\n    \n    # Host flag\n    df[\"home_is_host\"] = df[\"home_fifa_code\"].isin(HOSTS).astype(int)\n    df[\"away_is_host\"] = df[\"away_fifa_code\"].isin(HOSTS).astype(int)\n    \n    # Stage encoding\n    stage_order = {\"Group Stage\":0, \"Round of 16\":1, \"Quarter-final\":2, \"Semi-final\":3, \"Third-place play-off\":3, \"Final\":4}\n    df[\"stage_enc\"] = df[\"stage_name\"].map(stage_order).fillna(0)\n    \n    return df\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    df = build_match_features()\n    print(\"Feature matrix shape:\", df.shape)\n    print(\"Label distribution:\", df[\"label\"].value_counts().to_dict())\n    print(\"Elo diff stats:\", df[\"elo_diff\"].describe())\nPYEOF\necho \"features.py written\"","description":"Write feature engineering module"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":930,"cache_read_input_tokens":33416,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":930},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"280583a0-a049-4eb6-83aa-7a9742105563","uuid":"06d8948c-0aec-4493-a8b8-e31647f8f88b","request_id":"req_011CcVNgvbi8JnaVW87qYwCQ"}
