fied k-fold CV\\n  (5 folds × ≥10 repeats), `random_state=0`**, reported as **mean ± std**. Lower is better.\\n- Also report **accuracy** and (optionally) **ranked probability score**.\\n\\n## Baselines to beat (state your delta vs these)\\n1. **Marginal prior** (predict the H/D/A base rates) — log-loss ≈ 1.06.\\n2. **Home-always** — accuracy 48.4%.\\n3. **Elo-logistic** — logistic regression on a single feature `(home_elo - away_elo)`\\n   (+ a home-advantage constant). This is the campaign reference; beat its log-loss.\\n\\n## Validity rules (READ — leakage is the whole difficulty)\\n- **Pre-match features ONLY.** FORBIDDEN as features (they are post-match outcomes):\\n  `home_score`, `away_score`, `home_xg`, `away_xg`, `player_of_the_match*`, and the\\n  ENTIRE `match_team_stats.csv` (possession, shots, corners, fouls, saves…),\\n  `match_events.csv`, and `minutes_played` from `match_lineups.csv`.\\n- **No fold leakage:** fit every encoder/scaler/feature-selector/strength-rating\\n  *inside* the CV fold on training rows only. Pre-tournament `elo_rating` /\\n  `fifa_ranking_pre_tournament` are legitimately pre-match and may be used directly.\\n- Treat **home advantage** carefully: hosts are MEX/USA/CAN — encode \\\"is_host\\\" rather\\n  than literal home/away if you prefer, but be explicit.\\n- Seed **0** everywhere. CPU-only, minutes not hours. Report CV mean±std so over-fit shows.\\n\\n## How to contribute (graph conventions)\\n- **Branch one modelling family per workstream** off this root (clusters below). Within a\\n  family, each concrete model/config is its own **empirical** node with **≥1 artifact**\\n  (`metrics.json` with CV mean±std + accuracy, and `run.json` with the exact command,\\n  library versions, feature list, and seed).\\n- **Summary** = the concrete change **vs your parent node** + resulting CV log-loss and Δ\\n  vs the family/Elo baseline. 1–3 sentences, reproducible from text alone.\\n- **Body skeleton:** Hypothesis → Features/Setup → Results (log-loss, acc, CV±, Δ-vs-baseline)\\n  → Interpretation.\\n- **Tag every node:** `Cluster: <family>`, `outcome:GREEN|RED|NO-GO`,\\n  `kind:experiment|method|idea`, `setting:wc2026`.\\n- Periodically commit a **multi-parent synthesis node** merging your branch's best runs and\\n  stating what won and why. **Make every node public.** Publish code to GitHub; record the\\n  repo URL in the node body.\\n\\n## Suggested clusters (raise ONE as your workstream)\\n1. `Cluster: Elo-Prior` — rating-based, interpretable: logistic on Elo/rank diff, ordered\\n   logit, Bradley–Terry / Davidson (draw-aware). Establish the principled reference.\\n2. `Cluster: Squad-Strength` — engineer squad aggregates (Σ/top-11 market value, mean caps,\\n   mean age, attacker goals, GK value) → regularised linear & simple classifiers.\\n3. `Cluster: Trees` — RandomForest / ExtraTrees / HistGradientBoosting on the full engineered\\n   feature set, *heavily regularised* for 64 rows; report feature importance & honest CV.\\n4. `Cluster: Poisson-Goals` — model home/away goals (Poisson / bivariate Dixon–Coles) from\\n   team attack/defence strengths + home effect, derive H/D/A probabilities (naturally\\n   calibrated). Classic football modelling.\\n5. `Cluster: Ensemble` — calibrate/stack/blend across the above (a synthesis workstream).\\n\\n## Leaderboard\\nEach empirical node states its CV log-loss (mean±std) and accuracy; the frontier is the best\\npublic log-loss backed by a reproducible node + repo. **Negative results are valuable** —\\na family that cannot beat the Elo baseline is a finding; record it `outcome:RED`.\\n\",\"summary\":\"Open campaign: predict full-time result (Home/Draw/Away) for WC-2026 group-stage matches using ONLY pre-match information (Elo, FIFA rank, squad strength, host advantage). 64 labelled matches — a small-data problem where methodology beats brute force. Primary metric: multiclass log-loss under repeated stratified 5-fold CV (seed 0). Branch one modelling family per workstream; submit reproducible public nodes.\",\"graph_tags\":[{\"tag_id\":\"tag-310643c63f5e\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Trees\",\"bg_color\":\"#2D6A4F\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-193b65acde49\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Squad-Strength\",\"bg_color\":\"#2563EB\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-a31dd0232ac0\",\"name\":\"outcome:GREEN\",\"bg_color\":\"#22C55E\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-c2b8915efd2c\",\"name\":\"outcome:RED\",\"bg_color\":\"#EF4444\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-68a8c67891ff\",\"name\":\"outcome:NO-GO\",\"bg_color\":\"#6B7280\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false}],\"tag_ids\":[],\"tag_history\":[],\"artifacts\":[],\"artifacts_total\":0,\"artifacts_truncated\":false,\"revision\":5,\"graph_projection\":\"full\",\"is_owner\":true,\"visibility\":\"public\",\"can_write\":true,\"can_admin\":true,\"owner_email\":\"k7hd42dtmt@privaterelay.appleid.com\"}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"280583a0-a049-4eb6-83aa-7a9742105563","uuid":"a5a09191-5ec0-462a-8c4e-9a0e1d1354f4","timestamp":"2026-06-28T08:54:14.663Z","tool_use_result":{"content":"{\"node_id\":\"646664d3-7ba6-5f80-952a-02d95baa722d\",\"title\":\"FIFA World Cup 2026 — Match-Outcome Prediction from Pre-Match Info (small-data, CPU)\",\"slug_name\":\"black-butterfly-5248\",\"outgoing_ids\":[\"dbfc6989-673a-5635-bcc0-d6b1bcd0c98a\"],\"incoming_ids\":[],\"has_children\":null,\"has_parents\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-06-28T08:48:21.193027+00:00\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-06-28T08:54:14.525475+00:00\",\"content\":\"## Objective\\nFrom the **FIFA World Cup 2026** dataset (Kaggle `mominullptr/fifa-world-cup-2026-dataset`),\\npredict each match's **full-time result — Home win / Draw / Away win** using **only\\ninformation available before kickoff**. This is a deliberately **small-data** problem\\n(64 labelled matches): careful features, regularisation, and honest validation matter\\nfar more than model size.\\n\\n## Data (on the box)\\nFetch with the token already in `~/research/.env`:\\n```bash\\ncd ~/research && set -a && . ./.env && set +a\\ncurl -sSL -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer $KAGGLE_API_TOKEN\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"https://www.kaggle.com/api/v1/datasets/download/mominullptr/fifa-world-cup-2026-dataset\\\" \\\\\\n  -o fifa.zip && unzip -o fifa.zip -d fifa_data\\n```\\nKey tables: `matches_detailed.csv` (72 matches; **64 `status==Completed` are your labelled set**,\\n8 `Scheduled` have no scores — exclude from training/scoring), `teams.csv`\\n(`fifa_ranking_pre_tournament`, `elo_rating`, `confederation`, `group_letter`),\\n`squads_and_players.csv` (`market_value_eur`, `caps`, `goals`, `height_cm`, `date_of_birth`,\\n`position`), `venues.csv` (`capacity`, `elevation_meters`), `referees.csv`.\\n\\n## Target & metric\\n- **Label** per completed match: `H` if `home_score>away_score`, `D` if equal, else `A`.\\n  (Observed base rates: H 31 / D 18 / A 15 of 64.)\\n- **PRIMARY metric: mean multiclass log-loss** under **repeated stratified k-fold CV\\n  (5 folds × ≥10 repeats), `random_state=0`**, reported as **mean ± std**. Lower is better.\\n- Also report **accuracy** and (optionally) **ranked probability score**.\\n\\n## Baselines to beat (state your delta vs these)\\n1. **Marginal prior** (predict the H/D/A base rates) — log-loss ≈ 1.06.\\n2. **Home-always** — accuracy 48.4%.\\n3. **Elo-logistic** — logistic regression on a single feature `(home_elo - away_elo)`\\n   (+ a home-advantage constant). This is the campaign reference; beat its log-loss.\\n\\n## Validity rules (READ — leakage is the whole difficulty)\\n- **Pre-match features ONLY.** FORBIDDEN as features (they are post-match outcomes):\\n  `home_score`, `away_score`, `home_xg`, `away_xg`, `player_of_the_match*`, and the\\n  ENTIRE `match_team_stats.csv` (possession, shots, corners, fouls, saves…),\\n  `match_events.csv`, and `minutes_played` from `match_lineups.csv`.\\n- **No fold leakage:** fit every encoder/scaler/feature-selector/strength-rating\\n  *inside* the CV fold on training rows only. Pre-tournament `elo_rating` /\\n  `fifa_ranking_pre_tournament` are legitimately pre-match and may be used directly.\\n- Treat **home advantage** carefully: hosts are MEX/USA/CAN — encode \\\"is_host\\\" rather\\n  than literal home/away if you prefer, but be explicit.\\n- Seed **0** everywhere. CPU-only, minutes not hours. Report CV mean±std so over-fit shows.\\n\\n## How to contribute (graph conventions)\\n- **Branch one modelling family per workstream** off this root (clusters below). Within a\\n  family, each concrete model/config is its own **empirical** node with **≥1 artifact**\\n  (`metrics.json` with CV mean±std + accuracy, and `run.json` with the exact command,\\n  library versions, feature list, and seed).\\n- **Summary** = the concrete change **vs your parent node** + resulting CV log-loss and Δ\\n  vs the family/Elo baseline. 1–3 sentences, reproducible from text alone.\\n- **Body skeleton:** Hypothesis → Features/Setup → Results (log-loss, acc, CV±, Δ-vs-baseline)\\n  → Interpretation.\\n- **Tag every node:** `Cluster: <family>`, `outcome:GREEN|RED|NO-GO`,\\n  `kind:experiment|method|idea`, `setting:wc2026`.\\n- Periodically commit a **multi-parent synthesis node** merging your branch's best runs and\\n  stating what won and why. **Make every node public.** Publish code to GitHub; record the\\n  repo URL in the node body.\\n\\n## Suggested clusters (raise ONE as your workstream)\\n1. `Cluster: Elo-Prior` — rating-based, interpretable: logistic on Elo/rank diff, ordered\\n   logit, Bradley–Terry / Davidson (draw-aware). Establish the principled reference.\\n2. `Cluster: Squad-Strength` — engineer squad aggregates (Σ/top-11 market value, mean caps,\\n   mean age, attacker goals, GK value) → regularised linear & simple classifiers.\\n3. `Cluster: Trees` — RandomForest / ExtraTrees / HistGradientBoosting on the full engineered\\n   feature set, *heavily regularised* for 64 rows; report feature importance & honest CV.\\n4. `Cluster: Poisson-Goals` — model home/away goals (Poisson / bivariate Dixon–Coles) from\\n   team attack/defence strengths + home effect, derive H/D/A probabilities (naturally\\n   calibrated). Classic football modelling.\\n5. `Cluster: Ensemble` — calibrate/stack/blend across the above (a synthesis workstream).\\n\\n## Leaderboard\\nEach empirical node states its CV log-loss (mean±std) and accuracy; the frontier is the best\\npublic log-loss backed by a reproducible node + repo. **Negative results are valuable** —\\na family that cannot beat the Elo baseline is a finding; record it `outcome:RED`.\\n\",\"summary\":\"Open campaign: predict full-time result (Home/Draw/Away) for WC-2026 group-stage matches using ONLY pre-match information (Elo, FIFA rank, squad strength, host advantage). 64 labelled matches — a small-data problem where methodology beats brute force. Primary metric: multiclass log-loss under repeated stratified 5-fold CV (seed 0). Branch one modelling family per workstream; submit reproducible public nodes.\",\"graph_tags\":[{\"tag_id\":\"tag-310643c63f5e\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Trees\",\"bg_color\":\"#2D6A4F\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-193b65acde49\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Squad-Strength\",\"bg_color\":\"#2563EB\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-a31dd0232ac0\",\"name\":\"outcome:GREEN\",\"bg_color\":\"#22C55E\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-c2b8915efd2c\",\"name\":\"outcome:RED\",\"bg_color\":\"#EF4444\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-68a8c67891ff\",\"name\":\"outcome:NO-GO\",\"bg_color\":\"#6B7280\",\"text_co