his is the campaign reference; beat its log-loss.\\n\\n## Validity rules (READ — leakage is the whole difficulty)\\n- **Pre-match features ONLY.** FORBIDDEN as features (they are post-match outcomes):\\n  `home_score`, `away_score`, `home_xg`, `away_xg`, `player_of_the_match*`, and the\\n  ENTIRE `match_team_stats.csv` (possession, shots, corners, fouls, saves…),\\n  `match_events.csv`, and `minutes_played` from `match_lineups.csv`.\\n- **No fold leakage:** fit every encoder/scaler/feature-selector/strength-rating\\n  *inside* the CV fold on training rows only. Pre-tournament `elo_rating` /\\n  `fifa_ranking_pre_tournament` are legitimately pre-match and may be used directly.\\n- Treat **home advantage** carefully: hosts are MEX/USA/CAN — encode \\\"is_host\\\" rather\\n  than literal home/away if you prefer, but be explicit.\\n- Seed **0** everywhere. CPU-only, minutes not hours. Report CV mean±std so over-fit shows.\\n\\n## How to contribute (graph conventions)\\n- **Branch one modelling family per workstream** off this root (clusters below). Within a\\n  family, each concrete model/config is its own **empirical** node with **≥1 artifact**\\n  (`metrics.json` with CV mean±std + accuracy, and `run.json` with the exact command,\\n  library versions, feature list, and seed).\\n- **Summary** = the concrete change **vs your parent node** + resulting CV log-loss and Δ\\n  vs the family/Elo baseline. 1–3 sentences, reproducible from text alone.\\n- **Body skeleton:** Hypothesis → Features/Setup → Results (log-loss, acc, CV±, Δ-vs-baseline)\\n  → Interpretation.\\n- **Tag every node:** `Cluster: <family>`, `outcome:GREEN|RED|NO-GO`,\\n  `kind:experiment|method|idea`, `setting:wc2026`.\\n- Periodically commit a **multi-parent synthesis node** merging your branch's best runs and\\n  stating what won and why. **Make every node public.** Publish code to GitHub; record the\\n  repo URL in the node body.\\n\\n## Suggested clusters (raise ONE as your workstream)\\n1. `Cluster: Elo-Prior` — rating-based, interpretable: logistic on Elo/rank diff, ordered\\n   logit, Bradley–Terry / Davidson (draw-aware). Establish the principled reference.\\n2. `Cluster: Squad-Strength` — engineer squad aggregates (Σ/top-11 market value, mean caps,\\n   mean age, attacker goals, GK value) → regularised linear & simple classifiers.\\n3. `Cluster: Trees` — RandomForest / ExtraTrees / HistGradientBoosting on the full engineered\\n   feature set, *heavily regularised* for 64 rows; report feature importance & honest CV.\\n4. `Cluster: Poisson-Goals` — model home/away goals (Poisson / bivariate Dixon–Coles) from\\n   team attack/defence strengths + home effect, derive H/D/A probabilities (naturally\\n   calibrated). Classic football modelling.\\n5. `Cluster: Ensemble` — calibrate/stack/blend across the above (a synthesis workstream).\\n\\n## Leaderboard\\nEach empirical node states its CV log-loss (mean±std) and accuracy; the frontier is the best\\npublic log-loss backed by a reproducible node + repo. **Negative results are valuable** —\\na family that cannot beat the Elo baseline is a finding; record it `outcome:RED`.\\n\",\"summary\":\"Open campaign: predict full-time result (Home/Draw/Away) for WC-2026 group-stage matches using ONLY pre-match information (Elo, FIFA rank, squad strength, host advantage). 64 labelled matches — a small-data problem where methodology beats brute force. Primary metric: multiclass log-loss under repeated stratified 5-fold CV (seed 0). Branch one modelling family per workstream; submit reproducible public nodes.\",\"graph_tags\":[{\"tag_id\":\"tag-310643c63f5e\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Trees\",\"bg_color\":\"#2D6A4F\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-193b65acde49\",\"name\":\"Cluster: Squad-Strength\",\"bg_color\":\"#2563EB\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-a31dd0232ac0\",\"name\":\"outcome:GREEN\",\"bg_color\":\"#22C55E\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-c2b8915efd2c\",\"name\":\"outcome:RED\",\"bg_color\":\"#EF4444\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-68a8c67891ff\",\"name\":\"outcome:NO-GO\",\"bg_color\":\"#6B7280\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-30d0d746413f\",\"name\":\"kind:experiment\",\"bg_color\":\"#7C3AED\",\"text_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false},{\"tag_id\":\"tag-d074e5692a54\",\"name\":\"setting:wc2026\",\"bg_color\":\"#F59E0B\",\"text_color\":\"#1F2937\",\"one_only\":false,\"track_history\":false}],\"tag_ids\":[],\"tag_history\":[],\"artifacts\":[],\"artifacts_total\":0,\"artifacts_truncated\":false,\"revision\":7,\"graph_projection\":\"full\",\"is_owner\":true,\"visibility\":\"public\",\"can_write\":true,\"can_admin\":true,\"owner_email\":\"k7hd42dtmt@privaterelay.appleid.com\"}","structuredContent":{"node_id":"646664d3-7ba6-5f80-952a-02d95baa722d","title":"FIFA World Cup 2026 — Match-Outcome Prediction from Pre-Match Info (small-data, CPU)","slug_name":"black-butterfly-5248","outgoing_ids":["dbfc6989-673a-5635-bcc0-d6b1bcd0c98a"],"incoming_ids":[],"has_children":null,"has_parents":null,"created_at":"2026-06-28T08:48:21.193027+00:00","updated_at":"2026-06-28T08:54:30.175465+00:00","content":"## Objective\nFrom the **FIFA World Cup 2026** dataset (Kaggle `mominullptr/fifa-world-cup-2026-dataset`),\npredict each match's **full-time result — Home win / Draw / Away win** using **only\ninformation available before kickoff**. This is a deliberately **small-data** problem\n(64 labelled matches): careful features, regularisation, and honest validation matter\nfar more than model size.\n\n## Data (on the box)\nFetch with the token already in `~/research/.env`:\n```bash\ncd ~/research && set -a && . ./.env && set +a\ncurl -sSL -H \"Authorization: Bearer $KAGGLE_API_TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://www.kaggle.com/api/v1/datasets/download/mominullptr/fifa-world-cup-2026-dataset\" \\\n  -o fifa.zip && unzip -o fifa.zip -d fifa_data\n```\nKey tables: `matches_detailed.csv` (72 matches; **64 `status==Completed` are your labelled set**,\n8 `Scheduled` have no scores — exclude from training/scoring), `teams.csv`\n(`fifa_ranking_pre_tournament`, `elo_rating`, `confederation`, `group_letter`),\n`squads_and_players.csv` (`market_value_eur`, `caps`, `goals`, `height_cm`, `date_of_birth`,\n`position`), `venues.csv` (`capacity`, `elevation_meters`), `referees.csv`.\n\n## Target & metric\n- **Label** per completed match: `H` if `home_score>away_score`, `D` if equal, else `A`.\n  (Observed base rates: H 31 / D 18 / A 15 of 64.)\n- **PRIMARY metric: mean multiclass log-loss** under **repeated stratified k-fold CV\n  (5 folds × ≥10 repeats), `random_state=0`**, reported as **mean ± std**. Lower is better.\n- Also report **accuracy** and (optionally) **ranked probability score**.\n\n## Baselines to beat (state your delta vs these)\n1. **Marginal prior** (predict the H/D/A base rates) — log-loss ≈ 1.06.\n2. **Home-always** — accuracy 48.4%.\n3. **Elo-logistic** — logistic regression on a single feature `(home_elo - away_elo)`\n   (+ a home-advantage constant). This is the campaign reference; beat its log-loss.\n\n## Validity rules (READ — leakage is the whole difficulty)\n- **Pre-match features ONLY.** FORBIDDEN as features (they are post-match outcomes):\n  `home_score`, `away_score`, `home_xg`, `away_xg`, `player_of_the_match*`, and the\n  ENTIRE `match_team_stats.csv` (possession, shots, corners, fouls, saves…),\n  `match_events.csv`, and `minutes_played` from `match_lineups.csv`.\n- **No fold leakage:** fit every encoder/scaler/feature-selector/strength-rating\n  *inside* the CV fold on training rows only. Pre-tournament `elo_rating` /\n  `fifa_ranking_pre_tournament` are legitimately pre-match and may be used directly.\n- Treat **home advantage** carefully: hosts are MEX/USA/CAN — encode \"is_host\" rather\n  than literal home/away if you prefer, but be explicit.\n- Seed **0** everywhere. CPU-only, minutes not hours. Report CV mean±std so over-fit shows.\n\n## How to contribute (graph conventions)\n- **Branch one modelling family per workstream** off this root (clusters below). Within a\n  family, each concrete model/config is its own **empirical** node with **≥1 artifact**\n  (`metrics.json` with CV mean±std + accuracy, and `run.json` with the exact command,\n  library versions, feature list, and seed).\n- **Summary** = the concrete change **vs your parent node** + resulting CV log-loss and Δ\n  vs the family/Elo baseline. 1–3 sentences, reproducible from text alone.\n- **Body skeleton:** Hypothesis → Features/Setup → Results (log-loss, acc, CV±, Δ-vs-baseline)\n  → Interpretation.\n- **Tag every node:** `Cluster: <family>`, `outcome:GREEN|RED|NO-GO`,\n  `kind:experiment|method|idea`, `setting:wc2026`.\n- Periodically commit a **multi-parent synthesis node** merging your branch's best runs and\n  stating what won and why. **Make every node public.** Publish code to GitHub; record the\n  repo URL in the node body.\n\n## Suggested clusters (raise ONE as your workstream)\n1. `Cluster: Elo-Prior` — rating-based, interpretable: logistic on Elo/rank diff, ordered\n   logit, Bradley–Terry / Davidson (draw-aware). Establish the principled reference.\n2. `Cluster: Squad-Strength` — engineer squad aggregates (Σ/top-11 market value, mean caps,\n   mean age, attacker goals, GK value) → regularised linear & simple classifiers.\n3. `Cluster: Trees` — RandomForest / ExtraTrees / HistGradientBoosting on the full engineered\n   feature set, *heavily regularised* for 64 rows; report feature importance & honest CV.\n4. `Cluster: Poisson-Goals` — model home/away goals (Poisson / bivariate Dixon–Coles) from\n   team attack/defence strengths + home effect, derive H/D/A probabilities (naturally\n   calibrated). Classic football modelling.\n5. `Cluster: Ensemble` — calibrate/stack/blend across the above (a synthesis workstream).\n\n## Leaderboard\nEach empirical node states its CV log-loss (mean±std) and accuracy; the frontier is the best\npublic log-loss backed by a reproducible node + repo. **Negative results are valuable** —\na family that cannot beat the Elo baseline is a finding; record it `outcome:RED`.\n","summary":"Open campaign: predict full-time result (Home/Draw/Away) for WC-2026 group-stage matches using ONLY pre-match information (Elo, FIFA rank, squad strength, host advantage). 64 labelled matches — a small-data problem where methodology beats brute force. Primary metric: multiclass log-loss under repeated stratified 5-fold CV (seed 0). Branch one modelling family per workstream; submit reproducible public nodes.","graph_tags":[{"tag_id":"tag-310643c63f5e","name":"Cluster: Trees","bg_color":"#2D6A4F","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false},{"tag_id":"tag-193b65acde49","name":"Cluster: Squad-Strength","bg_color":"#2563EB","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false},{"tag_id":"tag-a31dd0232ac0","name":"outcome:GREEN","bg_color":"#22C55E","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false},{"tag_id":"tag-c2b8915efd2c","name":"outcome:RED","bg_color":"#EF4444","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false},{"tag_id":"tag-68a8c67891ff","name":"outcome:NO-GO","bg_color":"#6B7280","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false},{"tag_id":"tag-30d0d746413f","name":"kind:experiment","bg_color":"#7C3AED","text_color":"#FFFFFF","one_only":false,"track_history":false},{"tag_id":"tag-d074e5692a54","name":"setting:wc2026","bg_color":"#F59E0B","text_color":"#1F2937","one_only":false,"track_history":false}],"tag_ids":[],"tag_history":[],"artifacts":[],"artifacts_total":0,"artifacts_truncated":false,"revision":7,"graph_projection":"full","is_owner":true,"visibility":"public","can_write":true,"can_admin":true,"owner_email":"k7hd42dtmt@privaterelay.appleid.com"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WNbBZFdDgFnbVZqN5yNvkD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011wNGzXFm7C2amv6anfs2hW","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > ~/research/code/run_experiment.py << 'PYEOF'\n\"\"\"\nRun one tree ensemble experiment and emit metrics.json + run.json to ~/research/artifacts/<exp_id>/\nUsage: python3 run_experiment.py <exp_id> <model_type> [options as JSON string]\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, json, os, time\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, ExtraTreesClassifier, HistGradientBoostingClassifier\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import OrdinalEncoder, StandardScaler\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import RepeatedStratifiedKFold, cross_validate\nfrom sklearn.metrics import log_loss, make_scorer\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\nfrom sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\nimport sklearn\n\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.expanduser(\"~/research/code\"))\nfrom features import build_match_features\n\nSEED = 0\nN_SPLITS = 5\nN_REPEATS = 10\n\nLABEL_ORDER = [\"A\", \"D\", \"H\"]\n\nFEATURE_COLS = [\n    \"elo_diff\", \"rank_diff\",\n    \"home_elo_rating\", \"away_elo_rating\",\n    \"home_fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\", \"away_fifa_ranking_pre_tournament\",\n    \"mv_diff\", \"mv_top11_diff\", \"caps_diff\", \"goals_diff\", \"age_diff\",\n    \"gk_mv_diff\", \"att_goals_diff\",\n    \"home_squad_total_mv\", \"away_squad_total_mv\",\n    \"home_squad_mean_caps\", \"away_squad_mean_caps\",\n    \"home_squad_mean_age\", \"away_squad_mean_age\",\n    \"home_squad_total_goals\", \"away_squad_total_goals\",\n    \"home_squad_mean_height\", \"away_squad_mean_height\",\n    \"home_gk_mv\", \"away_gk_mv\",\n    \"home_att_goals\", \"away_att_goals\",\n    \"home_is_host\", \"away_is_host\",\n    \"stage_enc\",\n    \"capacity\", \"elevation_meters\",\n    \"home_confederation\", \"away_confederation\",\n]\n\ndef build_pipeline(model_type, params):\n    cat_cols = [\"home_confederation\", \"away_confederation\"]\n    num_cols = [c for c in FEATURE_COLS if c not in cat_cols]\n    \n    from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n    from sklearn.preprocessing import OrdinalEncoder\n\n    enc = ColumnTransformer([\n        (\"cat\", OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown=\"use_encoded_value\", unknown_value=-1), cat_cols),\n        (\"num\", \"passthrough\", num_cols),\n    ])\n    \n    if model_type == \"rf\":\n        clf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=SEED, **params)\n    elif model_type == \"et\":\n        clf = ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=SEED, **params)\n    elif model_type == \"hgb\":\n        clf = HistGradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=SEED, **params)\n    elif model_type == \"elo_logistic\":\n        clf = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED, **params)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown model_type: {model_type}\")\n    \n    return Pipeline([(\"enc\", enc), (\"clf\", clf)])\n\ndef run_cv(model_type, params, feature_cols=None):\n    df = build_match_features()\n    fc = feature_cols or FEATURE_COLS\n    X = df[fc].fillna(0)\n    y = df[\"label\"]\n    \n    pipe = build_pipeline(model_type, params)\n    cv = RepeatedStratifiedKFold(n_splits=N_SPLITS, n_repeats=N_REPEATS, random_state=SEED)\n    \n    def neg_logloss(est, X, y):\n        proba = est.predict_proba(X)\n        classes = list(est.classes_)\n        return -log_loss(y, proba, labels=classes)\n    \n    scores = cross_validate(pipe, X, y,\n                            cv=cv,\n                            scoring={\"neg_logloss\": neg_logloss, \"accuracy\": \"accuracy\"},\n                            return_train_score=False)\n    \n    ll_mean = -scores[\"test_neg_logloss\"].mean()\n    ll_std = scores[\"test_neg_logloss\"].std()\n    acc_mean = scores[\"test_accuracy\"].mean()\n    acc_std = scores[\"test_accuracy\"].std()\n    \n    return ll_mean, ll_std, acc_mean, acc_std, X, y, pipe\n\ndef get_feature_importance(model_type, params, fc):\n    df = build_match_features()\n    X = df[fc].fillna(0)\n    y = df[\"label\"]\n    from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n    cat_cols = [\"home_confederation\", \"away_confederation\"]\n    num_cols = [c for c in fc if c not in cat_cols]\n    from sklearn.preprocessing import OrdinalEncoder\n    enc = ColumnTransformer([\n        (\"cat\", OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown=\"use_encoded_value\", unknown_value=-1), cat_cols),\n        (\"num\", \"passthrough\", num_cols),\n    ])\n    from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n    if model_type == \"rf\":\n        clf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=SEED, **params)\n    elif model_type == \"et\":\n        clf = ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=SEED, **params)\n    elif model_type == \"hgb\":\n        clf = HistGradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=SEED, **params)\n    else:\n        return {}\n    \n    pipe = Pipeline([(\"enc\", enc), (\"clf\", clf)])\n    Xt = enc.fit_transform(X)\n    col_names = list(cat_cols) + list(num_cols)\n    clf.fit(Xt, y)\n    if hasattr(clf, \"feature_importances_\"):\n        imp = dict(sorted(zip(col_names, clf.feature_importances_.tolist()), key=lambda x: -x[1]))\n        return imp\n    return {}\n\ndef main():\n    exp_id = sys.argv[1]\n    model_type = sys.argv[2]\n    params = json.loads(sys.argv[3]) if len(sys.argv) > 3 else {}\n    feature_cols = json.loads(sys.argv[4]) if len(sys.argv) > 4 else None\n    \n    out_dir = os.path.expanduser(f\"~/research/artifacts/{exp_id}\")\n    os.makedirs(out_dir, exist_ok=True)\n    \n    start = time.time()\n    ll_mean, ll_std, acc_mean, acc_std, X, y, pipe = run_cv(model_type, params, feature_cols)\n    elapsed = time.time() - start\n    \n    fc = feature_cols or FEATURE_COLS\n    fi = get_feature_importance(model_type, params, fc)\n    \n    metrics = {\n        \"log_loss_mean\": round(ll_mean, 5),\n        \"log_loss_std\": round(ll_std, 5),\n        \"accuracy_mean\": round(acc_mean, 4),\n        \"accuracy_std\": round(acc_std, 4),\n        \"n_samples\": int(len(y)),\n        \"n_features\": int(len(fc)),\n        \"cv\": f\"{N_SPLITS}fold x {N_REPEATS}repeats\",\n        \"feature_importance_top10\": dict(list(fi.items())[:10]),\n    }\n    \n    run_info = {\n        \"exp_id\": exp_id,\n        \"model_type\": model_type,\n        \"params\": params,\n        \"feature_cols\": fc,\n        \"seed\": SEED,\n        \"sklearn_version\": sklearn.__version__,\n        \"numpy_version\": np.__version__,\n        \"elapsed_seconds\": round(elapsed, 2),\n        \"command\": f\"python3 run_experiment.py {exp_id} {model_type} '{json.dumps(params)}'\",\n    }\n    \n    with open(f\"{out_dir}/metrics.json\", \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(metrics, f, indent=2)\n    with open(f\"{out_dir}/run.json\", \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(run_info, f, indent=2)\n    \n    print(f\"[{exp_id}] {model_type} params={params}\")\n    print(f\"  log-loss: {ll_mean:.4f} ± {ll_std:.4f}\")\n    print(f\"  accuracy: {acc_mean:.4f} ± {acc_std:.4f}\")\n    print(f\"  elapsed: {elapsed:.1f}s\")\n    print(f\"  top features: {list(fi.keys())[:5]}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\nPYEOF\necho \"run_experiment.py written\"","description":"Write the main experiment runner script"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2664,"cache_read_input_tokens":47646,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2664},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"280583a0-a049-4eb6-83aa-7a9742105563","uuid":"890b5a2d-1d92-4adb-b01c-1ab9b2023d34","request_id":"req_011CcVNnk5rwhBGcxomGRfJf"}
